plotutils.menu.guide.advanced_body=§9Advanced Utilities§r collects admin and diagnostic tools.\n\n§dVisualize Global§r shows all available areas for admins.\n\n§9Addon Data§r lets you inspect counts, reload data, and clear stuck sessions. Use it carefully: delete actions ask for confirmation because they affect saved data.\n\n§eRecommendation:§r before destructive actions, close nearby players' toolboxes and make sure nobody is creating plots.
plotutils.menu.guide.advanced_title=Advanced Guide
plotutils.menu.guide.create_body=§aStep 1:§r mark two corners with the §bSelection Wand§r. The plot includes every block between those corners.\n\n§aStep 2:§r open §aCreate Plot§r. Review the size, owner, and internal ID. The §eID§r should be short, unique, and have no spaces.\n\n§aStep 3:§r if the plot is inside a §6group§r, confirm whether it should be assigned to that group.\n\n§cImportant:§r if the selection overlaps another plot or sits partly outside a group, the addon will warn you before saving.
plotutils.menu.guide.create_title=Create Plot Guide
plotutils.menu.guide.group_create_body=Mark two corners with the §bSelection Wand§r to define the §6group§r area.\n\nThe §avisible name§r is what players see in menus; the §einternal ID§r is optional and is generated from the name if you leave it blank.\n\nUse §ePlot Config§r to review the §earea rules§r this group will start with.\n\nIf plots are inside the area, the form tells you how many are §afully inside§r and whether any are §cpartially crossed§r.\n\n§cAvoid saving§r when plots are partially crossed: that usually makes rules and visualization harder to understand.
plotutils.menu.guide.group_create_title=Create Group Guide
plotutils.menu.guide.main_body=§6Plot Utils§r organizes your tools into sections.\n\n§aCreate Plot§r: use the §bSelection Wand§r to mark two corners, then review the name, owner, and rules before finishing.\n\n§bMy Plots§r: open your plot list, teleport, change owner, manage members, or delete plots.\n\n§dVisualize§r: shows boundaries in the world. §eSneak + use§r the Visualize tool to pick what it shows: plots, groups, or all.\n\n§eConfig§r: changes global permissions or defaults. New defaults apply to future plots; existing plots are managed from their own menu.\n\n§6Groups§r combine several plots inside a larger area and can protect that whole area. §9Advanced§r contains maintenance and addon data tools.
plotutils.menu.guide.main_title=Toolbox Guide
plotutils.menu.guide.plot_groups_body=§6Groups§r help manage large areas that contain several plots, and can protect the whole area.\n\n§aNew Group Area§r: mark an area with the §bWand§r, then use §ePlot Config§r to review the area rules before creating. You can delete plots fully inside it when reorganizing.\n\n§bGroup List§r: review existing groups, rename them, edit §eArea Rules§r, view their plots, or delete the group.\n\n§eArea Rules§r protect everything inside the group except the plots it contains; inside a plot, that plot's own rules apply.\n\n§dVisualize Groups§r helps separate group borders from plot borders. §eSneak + use§r the visualize tool to switch modes.\n\n§eTip:§r create the large group first, then create plots inside it.
plotutils.menu.guide.plot_groups_title=Groups Guide
