plotutils.support.plot_creation_started=Mark two corners with the wand. When complete, §aCreate Plot§r and §ePlot Config§r appear. You can §cdrop the wand§r to cancel and clear the current selection.
plotutils.support.plot_selection_complete=Selection complete. Review §ePlot Config§r to choose visitor permissions, then use §aCreate Plot§r when ready.
plotutils.support.group_creation_started=Mark two corners for the group. When complete, use §ePlot Config§r to review its rules and §aCreate Group§r to save it.
plotutils.support.groups_menu=Groups organize several plots inside a larger area. The yellow group area can apply rules outside contained plots; each plot still controls its own permissions inside. From here you can create, list, configure, and visualize groups.
plotutils.support.group_selection_complete=Group area complete. Review its configuration before creating it. Plots must be fully contained; a red border means conflict.
plotutils.support.advanced=§eWarning:§r this section contains administrative and diagnostic tools. Global visualization can display many areas; Addon Data can reload, restore sessions, and delete information. Read confirmations carefully.
plotutils.support.visualize_plots=§aGreen§r shows normal plots and §dpurple§r identifies plots belonging to a group. §cRed§r indicates an invalid intersection with your selection.
plotutils.support.visualize_groups=§eYellow§r represents the full group boundary. Its plots appear §dpurple§r to distinguish them from the general area; §cred§r signals a conflict.
plotutils.support.visualize_global=Global visualization combines everything: §agreen§r = plots, §eyellow§r = groups, §dpurple§r = grouped plots, §6orange§r = warning, and §cred§r = conflict.
